<h2 id="salon-needs">What Multi-Location Salons Actually Need</h2>

I've deployed guest WiFi across salon and spa venues as part of our business. Salon operators face a specific set of challenges that generic business software handles poorly:

<ul>
  <li><strong>Appointment-based revenue</strong> -- every empty chair is lost income, so booking and scheduling must be airtight</li>
  <li><strong>Stylist/provider management</strong> -- commission structures, individual schedules, service menus that vary by provider skill level</li>
  <li><strong>Client relationships</strong> -- repeat clients are the business, so tracking preferences, visit history, and rebooking is critical</li>
  <li><strong>Walk-in vs appointment balance</strong> -- especially at multi-location chains where capacity varies by location and time</li>
  <li><strong>Review management</strong> -- one bad Google review can crater a location's bookings for weeks</li>
</ul>

Here's what works for each category.

<h2 id="booking">Booking &amp; Scheduling</h2>

<h3>Vagaro -- Best All-in-One for Salons</h3>

Vagaro is purpose-built for salons, spas, and fitness studios. It combines booking, POS, payroll, marketing, and client management in one platform. For salon operators who want fewer tools to manage, Vagaro handles more under one roof than any competitor at this price.

The booking system handles online scheduling, walk-ins, waitlists, recurring appointments, and multi-provider calendars. Clients can book specific stylists, view availability across locations, and receive automated confirmations and reminders. The POS integrates directly so checkout is seamless.

Multi-location management lets you see all locations from one dashboard, transfer client records between units, and run reports across the chain.

<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $30/mo per location for booking + POS, additional features priced per module.</p>

