  Try Vagaro Free for One Month &rarr;
</a>

<h3>Square Appointments -- Best for Simpler Operations</h3>

If you don't need Vagaro's full suite, Square Appointments provides solid booking and POS for salon chains at a lower price. The free tier works for single providers, and the Plus plan at $29/mo per location adds multi-staff scheduling, resource management, and automated reminders.

Square's advantage is ecosystem. If you're already using Square for payments, adding Appointments keeps everything in one system -- POS, booking, payments, payroll, and marketing.

<p><strong>Cost:</strong> Free for individuals, $29/mo per location for Plus.</p>

<a href="https://operatorstack.tech/recommends/square" class="affiliate-cta">
  Try Square Appointments Free &rarr;
</a>

<h2 id="crm">CRM: GoHighLevel -- $297/mo</h2>

Most salon booking systems have basic client management but lack the automation depth that multi-location chains need. GoHighLevel fills that gap.

<p><strong>Where GHL adds value for salons:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Automated review requests</strong> -- after every appointment, trigger an SMS asking for a Google review. At scale, this builds review volume across all locations systematically</li>
  <li><strong>No-show follow-up</strong> -- automated sequences that re-engage clients who missed appointments without staff having to remember</li>
  <li><strong>Rebooking campaigns</strong> -- tag clients who haven't visited in 60/90/120 days and trigger a re-engagement sequence with a booking link</li>
  <li><strong>New client welcome</strong> -- automated welcome sequence after first visit with service recommendations based on what they booked</li>
  <li><strong>Referral tracking</strong> -- track which clients refer new bookings and reward them automatically</li>
</ul>

Each location gets its own sub-account. Build these workflows once, Snapshot them to every new location. The salon group I've worked with most closely went from manually texting no-shows to a fully automated system that recovered roughly 30% of missed appointments.

<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $297/mo for unlimited locations.</p>

