<h2 id="payroll">Payroll: Gusto -- $40/mo + $6/employee</h2>

Salon payroll is uniquely complex. Commission structures, booth rental vs employment, tip tracking, product sales commissions, and multi-state compliance if you operate across state lines. Gusto handles all of it.

For salon chains specifically, Gusto's flexible pay structures support the mixed compensation models common in the industry -- base pay plus commission plus tips, or straight commission, or booth rental arrangements. The multi-location support means one payroll run covers every unit.

The alternative is outsourcing to a payroll service at $200+/mo or spending hours per pay period doing it manually. At $40/mo base plus $6 per employee, Gusto is the clear value play.

<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $40/mo base + $6/mo per employee.</p>

<a href="https://operatorstack.tech/recommends/gusto" class="affiliate-cta">
  Try Gusto Free for One Month &rarr;
