<h2 id="wifi">WiFi: Ubiquiti UniFi</h2>

Guest WiFi in salons serves two purposes: client experience during longer appointments (color processing, treatments) and data capture for your email list. A client who logs into WiFi through a captive portal gives you their email address -- which flows directly into AWeber or GoHighLevel.

Ubiquiti UniFi access points provide commercial-grade coverage with zero monthly fees. The U6 Lite is typically sufficient for salon spaces. The UniFi controller manages all locations centrally, and the captive portal integration turns every WiFi login into a list-building opportunity.

I've deployed this exact setup across multiple salon venues. The WiFi-to-email pipeline typically adds 50-200 new email subscribers per location per month with zero effort from staff.

<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $100-250 per venue (hardware only), $0/mo ongoing.</p>

